in our broadcasting station.

78
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,160
(But even so, you can't just hire
someone because of that.)

79
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,400
Yes, I know. That's why she's an intern.

80
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,480
A variety show is
all about keeping up with the trends.

81
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,440
She was frozen for 20 years.

82
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,960
How can someone like her participate
in making a variety show?

83
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,320
Ms. Yoon, do you remember
what you said in our first meeting?

84
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,320
You told me that I'm the reason
why you decided to join this show.

85
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,600
You told me you trust me.

86
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:37,800
I was also in a capsule
for the past 20 years.

87
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,520
So why do you trust me
when I'm old-school as well?

88
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,520
-That's because--
-The reason why I chose you

89
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,120
among all the other competent writers

90
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,720
is because I saw something in you.

91
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,240
When it comes to people I'll work
with such as the assistant director,

92
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,360
writers, camera, and audio crew members,

93
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,040
I am very picky.

94
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,200
If I didn't think you could do it,

95
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,920
I wouldn't have given you a chance.

96
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:01,640
If you trust me,

97
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,920
trust in my judgment as well.

98
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:07,160
After that, you may judge as you like.

99
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,080
Don't give me such looks of disapproval.

100
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,680
Just say it to my face.

101
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,600
If I catch you talking about this
behind my back,

102
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,960
I will make sure you all pay for it.

103
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:20,360
I'm pretty good at talking down to others.

104
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:23,200
Then is she our junior or senior?

105
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,560
Based on her age, she's--

106
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,120
Why is that important?

107
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,400
-What?
-This industry is based

108
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,120
on our achievements and outcomes.

109
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,640
She's 44 years old
and hasn't been working.

110
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,960
She's an intern with
no experience in this field.

111
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:39,080
Focus on what you can do,
so you don't fall behind.

112
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,880
Let's resume our meeting.

113
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,800
Hello.

114
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,600
I'm the assistant director for
"Go Go 99" at TBO, Ko Mi-ran.

115
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,600
I called to ask about the location.

116
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,840
