00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,440
I'm going to get a divorce,
then start over with Mi-ran.

262
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,680
I mean it.

263
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,200
Father, I want to get Mi-ran
back in my life.

264
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,520
Honey.

265
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:50,240
Listen, you playboy professor.

266
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:53,000
-I'll call the police.
-Honey. Honey.

267
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,800
-Mom!
-Don't stop me.

268
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,280
The Internet is going crazy

269
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,200
about Mi-ran.

270
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,960
They found out she participated
in the cryonics experiment.

271
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,160
-What?
-What?

272
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,360
But they're all encouraging her.

273
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,000
There are

274
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:10,960
21,473 likes.

275
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,480
She's so awesome.

276
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:20,400
Here are the headlines for today.

277
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,800
("Chairman Lee Seok-du's wife,
Park Hyo-woo Dies from Heart Attack")

278
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:24,960
What is this?

279
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,920
Chairman Lee's wife died?

280
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,920
Yes. His wife Park Hyo Woo passed away

281
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,680
due to a heart attack.

282
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,280
What a sad coincidence.

283
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,880
The wife of the person
you wanted me to look into suddenly died.

284
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,600
We better go to her funeral.

285
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,160
It'll be a family-only funeral.

286
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:43,920
There is no information about it,

287
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,800
and the news came to us
through an unofficial route.

288
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:47,960
She died suddenly,

289
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,760
but I find it strange that
the police aren't investigating.

290
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,720
You recorded her voice then, right?

291
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,320
-I did.
-We should air it on the news.

292
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:59,080
She told me not to.
She asked me to keep it confidential.

293
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,800
No. If it's kept confidential,

294
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,440
the investigation won't happen.

295
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,520
We must find out who it is.

296
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,240
Did you get your memories back?

297
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,040
No.

298
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:14,800
I just remembered a snippet of it.

299
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:19,000
All I could remember was that
there was something like this.

300
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,960
I don't have all of my memories back.

301
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,160
In case

302
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,320
something happens to me,

303
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,240
you should hold onto this.

304
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,120
(I need to go somewhere.)

305
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,080
(There's less than two hours
until the defrosting.)

306
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,240
(I'll be back before then.)

307
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,480
(Help me, Professor Yoon.)

308
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:22,600
Professor Hwang.

309
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:26,960
Don't tell anyone that I'm here.

310
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,960
Even to Director Ma? He should know.

311
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:32,640
Yes. We should tell him.

312
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,120
I need to tell him
what I couldn't back then.

313
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,600
I need to tell him who tried to kill me.

314
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,440
Professor Hwang.

315
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,800
Did your memories come back?

316
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,080
(Hello, I'm Ko Mi-ran.)

317
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,200
(From Ko Mi-ran, a 31.5℃ cryonics woman.)

318
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,640
Professor Hwang Gab-su is alive.

319
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,760
Professor Hwang needs
to regain his memories

320
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:17,320
for things to become clear.

321
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:21,280
(The person Detective Baek Young-tak
requested guards for)

322
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,840
(was Professor Hwang.)

323
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:26,600
Where has Hwang Gab-su been all this time?

324
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,240
Since he's an American citizen,

325
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,800
he doesn't have a residence in Korea.

326
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,080
He had been hiding in Ko Mi-ran's house.

327
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,280
"Ko Mi-ran"?

328
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,760
The cryonic woman?

329
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:56,040
Here's the confirmed list of those
who will be appearing on the show.

330
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,880
The assistant director is in charge

331
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:03,080
of paying the fees
and handling their schedules.

332
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:05,080
Yes, ma'am.

333
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,960
-Let's do our best.
-Okay.

334
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:32,960
(Ko Mi-ran, good job!)

335
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:35,080
Ko Mi-ran, good job.

336
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,480
(Confirmed Cast List,
Professor Hwang Dong-hyuk)

337
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:54,640
This Hwang Dong-hyuk isn't
the Hwang Byung-sim I know, right?

338
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,560
No way.

339
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,720
It can't be.

340
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,480
(Psychological Consultant)

341
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:03,320
What is it?

342
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:11,600
(Editing Room A)

343
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:20,000
-Hello?
(-Dong-chan.)

344
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:23,040
(I found the current address and phone
number of the person you asked for.)

345
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:25,480
-Did you really find the person?
(-I did.)

346
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:28,600
Can you text the information to me?

347
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:50,560
Okay. I'll call when I'm nearby. Bye.

348
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:55,960
Hey--

349
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,520
Who is that punk?

350
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,800
Who is she smiling at?

351
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,680
Why isn't she working?

352
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,000
Mi-ran, you...

353
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:14,560
I look so pathetic right now.

354
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:17,320
But...

355
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:19,320
-Should we keep on tracking it?
-Gosh.

356
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,480
You startled me!

357
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:22,480
Can you make some noise
before you talk to me?

358
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:23,920
You gave me a heart attack.

359
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,720
I made a sound when I spoke to you.

360
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:29,040
Then should I have yelled,
"Here I come" or something?

361
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:32,160
Who's that guy over there

362
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,480
smiling next to Mi-ran?

363
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,000
He's the newest intern in your team.

364
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:37,000
He's 1 of the 10 interns
that got in this time.

365
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:38,640
He's really smart and hardworking.

366
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,120
All the interns are gathered today.

367
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:42,320
-How old is that punk?
-He's in his first year.

368
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:44,600
What? He's 20?

369
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,480
By the way, why are you calling

370
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:48,440
someone's precious son a punk?

371
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:50,120
What happened to your personality?

372
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:54,440
Look at how much she's smiling
in front of that young man.

373
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,960
About that middle school student

374
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:58,280
I spoke with the owner of the ID
that posted about Mi-Ran,

375
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:00,320
and I've never heard someone
swear so much.

376
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,200
Every other word she said was a curse.

377
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,000
She said she'd find the person
who stole her ID

378
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,120
and pull out their eyeballs.
She made such a big deal.

379
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,960
She might find the culprit
on her own then.

380
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:10,400
-I think so.
-What are you saying?

381
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:12,440
Are you going to leave it to
that foul-mouthed student?

382
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,760
I'm happy that we'll be working together.

383
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:23,080
I'm still going to treat you the same.

384
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:26,840
You seemed special
from the moment I met you.

385
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,280
You're not like girls these days.

386
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,120
That's why I liked it.

387
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:34,480
Were you surprised?

388
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,480
Mi-ran, I'll help you.

389
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,440
Who cares if you're 44 or 24?

390
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,640
I'll treat you the same as before.

391
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,120
Thank you, Ji-hun.

392
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:51,160
I found out that my mom knows you.

393
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,960
I didn't want to ask, so I didn't.

394
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:57,720
But now I think I know.

395
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:00,200
You're my mom's friend, aren't you?

396
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,000
-Your mom?
-I think I heard about you from her.

397
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:07,360
She said that she and Aunt Kyung-ja
were close to another person,

398
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:09,440
but they suddenly disappeared.

399
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:11,360
Aunt Kyung-ja?

400
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:17,240
Is your mom's name Oh Young-sun?

401
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,160
Yes.

402
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:22,000
You're Young-sun's son?

403
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,040
Yes, Mi-ran. Isn't it funny?

404
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,520
Wait.

405
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,240
Then...

406
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,080
Does that mean Hwang Byung-sim
is your father?

407
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:37,920
Yes, that's my dad's old name.

408
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:42,640
You know my dad as well?

409
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,320
Are you also friends with him?

410
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,200
So you're telling me

411
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,680
that you're Byung-sim's son?

412
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,680
Mi-ran.

413
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:15,520
Bring over a chair and sit down.

414
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,680
I have something to tell you.

415
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,520
Okay.

416
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:29,040
I probably should've
told you this earlier.

417
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:32,600
I'd like to tell you something in advance

418
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:34,560
as Dong-chan's former assistant director.

419
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:36,920
Okay.

420
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:44,160
It's nice to see you take notes.

421
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,520
When you're
Dong-chan's assistant director,

422
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:49,680
there are moments
when you shouldn't be too honest.

423
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,440
First, when he asks,

424
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:53,920
"Are you tired?"

425
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,400
-Good work.
-Good work.

426
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,600
-Thanks, guys. -Good work.

427
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,920
-Good work.
-Good work.

428
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,320
Good work.

429
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,800
Are you tired?

430
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,560
Yes, I'm tired.

431
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,800
Do you think you're the only one?
I'm tired as well, you know.

432
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,080
Plus, you didn't even do anything.

433
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:12,000
If this is enough to make you tired,
how will you finish the rest of the shoot?

434
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:14,720
If that's the best you can do,
just quit your job.

435
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,960
Go home and watch TV as a viewer.

436
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:21,040
(Don't ever tell him that you're tired.)

437
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:25,480
Second,

438
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:28,520
if he asks, "What do you think
our ratings will be?"

439
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:30,600
What do you think our ratings will be?

440
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:43,320
About 15 percent?

441
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,600
We have three more months
until the show airs,

442
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:52,320
but your target is only 15 percent?

443
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:55,920
Are you saying you're only going
to work hard enough to reach 15 percent?

444
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:56,960
No, that's not it...

445
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,360
Are you working with me to make
a show that only gets 15 percent?

446
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,640
What do you take me for?

447
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:02,000
Do you want me to retire?

448
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:05,000
-No, that's not it.
-Then what is it?

449
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:10,680
You need to tell him a high number
even if it seems unrealistic.

450
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:13,480
Then he becomes happy
and starts complimenting you.

451
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,280
If you manage to evade all of those
situations,

452
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,280
he'll eventually be the first one
to get exhausted.

453
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:19,080
Dong-chan may not seem like it,

454
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,680
but he's not very persistent.

455
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,280
Oh, I see.

456
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:23,600
The questions he asks

457
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,760
are like the riddles of the Sphinx.

458
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:27,280
He doesn't even know the answers,

459
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:29,640
but he asks them anyway.
And if he doesn't like your answer,

460
00:29:29,720 --> 00:29:31,520
he just sucks the life out of you.

461
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:35,520
Okay, I'll keep that in mind.

462
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:38,080
By the way, do you know

463
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:40,600
who casted
Professor Hwang Dong-hyuk and why?

464
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:44,200
After Dong-chan saw
the absurd video clip he uploaded

465
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,760
on the official webpage of "Go Go 99",

466
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:48,440
Dong-chan thought
he'd be great for the show.

467
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,440
When you're a director of a variety show,

468
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,920
it's your job to cast peculiar organisms.

469
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,720
I personally don't think

470
00:29:56,040 --> 00:29:57,480
it's a good idea.

471
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:58,760
Do you know him?

472
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,040
Well

473
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,240
-Why don't you reconsider--
-Wait.

474
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:06,120
Hello? Oh, really?

475
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,120
Did the stock price increase today?

476
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,960
Darn it. It declined?

477
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,960
But you told me it'll rise.

478
00:30:24,040 --> 00:30:25,160
One, two.

479
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,600
Kim Jin?

480
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,280
Dong-chan!

481
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,560
I really wanted to
know how you were doing,

482
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:46,080
and I wanted to call,

483
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,600
but I promised the chief...

484
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,040
Oh, wait. He's the president now. Right?

485
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:50,920
Yes.

486
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,600
I promised him that
I'd never talk about the experiment.

487
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,280
I know. You don't have to explain.

488
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,440
This is so cool.

489
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,320
That experiment really wasn't a joke.

490
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:03,800
You look exactly
like you did 20 years ago.

491
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:05,880
I told you that it wasn't a joke.

492
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,200
To be honest,
I had my doubts about the experiment.

493
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:11,560
Everyone did.

494
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:15,440
You taught me how
to use a camera properly back then,

495
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:17,000
and that totally changed my life.

496
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,240
Thanks to you,

497
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:20,960
I managed to become
a successful photographer.

498
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,200
It was a confidential project.

499
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,440
I couldn't hire a proper cameraman,

500
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:27,440
and you seemed like
the most trustworthy guy.

501
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:28,760
I was right, wasn't I?

502
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:31,240
Although I didn't know
you'd keep quiet about it for 20 years.

503
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:33,960
But why did you want to see me?

504
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,680
By any chance,

505
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:42,840
do you still have the tape of
what you filmed then?

506
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:46,480
Okay, I'll call you back. Bye.

507
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,120
I wonder what's wrong.

508
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:17,080
Hello, everyone.

509
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:19,680
You're watching "Newsline",
and this is Na Ha-young.

510
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,800
A recent online post about Ko Mi-ran,

511
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,520
a participant of the cryonics experiment,

512
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:25,320
has caused a huge controversy.

513
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:28,800
Why did the broadcasting station
keep her identity a secret?

514
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:31,520
It was because the broadcasting station

515
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:34,560
wanted to protect her
from an unknown threat.

516
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:37,720
(This is a video of the explosion
of Professor Jo Gi-bum,)

