00:32:51,760 --> 00:32:54,040
However, we've come to a conclusion

522
00:32:54,120 --> 00:32:56,880
that our main priority is
to protect everyone who was involved

523
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,520
in the cryonics experiment.

524
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:02,080
Therefore, we are now going
to reveal the informant's voice.

525
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:06,000
(I know who bombed Professor Jo's car.)

526
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:09,120
(I know who the culprit is.)

527
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:12,480
(No, don't do that.)

528
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:15,800
(I'll just meet you
at the broadcasting station.)

529
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,480
-What is this?
(-But there's one condition.)

530
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:20,360
-What's going on?
(-I want Director Ma Dong-chan)

531
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,480
(to come with you.)

532
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:25,120
(Please save my husband.
The cryonic capsule--)

533
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:27,160
Ever since this last phone call,

534
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:29,800
we haven't been able
to hear from the informant.

535
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:32,200
She is our only clue
to find out who's behind these threats.

536
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:34,200
If anyone happens to
recognize this woman's voice,

537
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:37,400
(please call the News Bureau at TBO
and tell us who she is.)

538
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,320
(Ko Mi-ran)

539
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:54,200
(The receiver cannot be reached.
Please leave a message--)

540
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:57,080
My gosh, why isn't she picking up?

541
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:39,120
I saw the news. Thanks for that.

542
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:41,679
"Thanks"?

543
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:44,760
You're talking to the news bureau chief.

544
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,560
-Ha-young.
-What do you think

545
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:49,000
would've happened to us

546
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,360
if I had stopped you
from doing that experiment,

547
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,560
and you didn't do it?

548
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,880
-There's no point in talking about that.
-Then what's worth talking about?

549
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,680
Are we not allowed to talk to each other

550
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:04,600
about anything else other than the news?

551
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:07,320
Do you know what the only regret
I have is?

552
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:12,720
It's not being able to stop you
from doing that experiment.

553
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:13,920
What about you?

554
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,080
Don't you regret it?

555
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:18,880
Ha-young.

556
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:25,800
From now on, don't look back.

557
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:29,520
Live a life that makes you happy.

558
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,640
(Ko Mi-ran)

559
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:06,840
(Cold-hearted Punk)

560
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:19,720
Hey, Mi-ran.

561
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,160
Mi-ran.

562
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,880
Where did she go?

563
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,600
(I think I have a cold.
I'm going to get some rest.)

564
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:42,280
(I think I have a cold.)

565
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,600
(I'm going to get some rest.)

566
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:49,800
Are you sure it's a cold?

567
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:04,280
Did you take the shot?

568
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:06,080
I did.

569
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:09,720
I'm relieved.

570
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:14,120
I guess

571
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:17,120
we catch colds

572
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:20,160
like everyone else.

573
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,000
I guess

574
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:26,200
we can die

575
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,520
like everyone else.

576
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,560
But still,

577
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:37,320
you shouldn't get sick. I told you not to.

578
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:40,680
You really don't listen, do you?

579
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:43,560
Shouldn't we

580
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,840
keep a distance of 50cm?

581
00:38:48,080 --> 00:38:50,560
We're too close now.

582
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,400
I can't be

583
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,080
any farther away from you.

584
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:22,440
Let's

585
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:25,960
just go with it.

586
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:30,160
Let's not feign ignorance.

587
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:33,120
Let's just

588
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:36,120
do this.

589
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,880
Mr. Ma.

590
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:43,480
Then

591
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:45,880
can I like you?

592
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:50,920
If I say no,

593
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,440
will you stop?

594
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,360
But

595
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,560
why are you always doing things first?

596
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,680
You shouldn't have said that first.

597
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,680
Then what should I do?

598
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:14,200
What do you mean?

599
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:18,920
You just need

600
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:22,440
to like me as well.

601
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,000
Tell me.

602
00:42:36,040 --> 00:42:37,800
There's something you need to tell me.

603
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:39,640
You go first.

604
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:41,520
You have something to tell me.

605
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:44,360
I have so much to say.

606
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:47,640
I don't know where to begin.

607
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,560
-So--
-How do Dad and Mi-ran

608
00:42:50,520 --> 00:42:51,840
know each other?

609
00:42:53,440 --> 00:42:54,960
What is their--

610
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,520
She's his first love.

611
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:01,600
Because of that friend of yours,

612
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,600
your dad wants to divorce me.

613
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,760
Do you like her?

614
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:11,040
No, right?

615
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:17,680
How could you?

616
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:54,000
You're not pretending
like it doesn't work, are you?

617
00:43:54,280 --> 00:43:56,120
I'm not that type.

618
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:57,880
-It's too tight.
-Hold on.

619
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:08,600
Hold on.

620
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:12,560
There.

621
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:25,520
You can look at me like that
during the day,

622
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:28,240
but don't do it at night.

623
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:32,080
I'm much healthier than you think.

624
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,280
Hey, come on. Mi-ran.

625
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:40,640
Yes?

626
00:44:42,440 --> 00:44:45,760
The face you see in the mirror

627
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:49,160
and the one I see are different.

628
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:55,440
You're pretty, so don't smile like that.

629
00:45:12,680 --> 00:45:14,880
We're going to the location tomorrow,
so I'll come pick you up.

630
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:17,760
Sleep tight.
Don't forget your fever-reducing shot.

631
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:20,560
-Okay.
-Bye.

632
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,160
He said I'm pretty.

633
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:09,200
I'll keep it short.

634
00:47:09,280 --> 00:47:10,320
What?

635
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:13,520
Cut the power supply off

636
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:16,280
for the cryonic capsules in your lab.

637
00:47:18,680 --> 00:47:20,920
We need to make the cryonics experiment

638
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:24,080
a failed experiment.

639
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:28,440
I can't... I can't do that.

640
00:47:28,520 --> 00:47:30,280
Then you'll die.

641
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:31,480
Not in a cryonic capsule,

642
00:47:31,560 --> 00:47:33,960
but in a real freezer.

643
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:35,200
Why are you

644
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:38,200
doing this to me?

645
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:47,560
You don't have a choice.

646
00:47:47,640 --> 00:47:49,560
Just do as I say.

647
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:52,240
If you don't do it, I'll do it myself.

648
00:47:52,520 --> 00:47:56,040
The survivors, Ma Dong-chan and Ko Mi-ran,

649
00:47:57,040 --> 00:48:00,000
will also die.

650
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:56,520
You're good. Let's go.

651
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:08,320
Hello?

652
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:10,320
(Is this Ms. Ko Mi-ran's phone?)

653
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:11,760
Yes, that's me.

654
00:49:11,880 --> 00:49:14,080
(I'm a cultural communications professor,)

655
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:15,600
(Seo Hyun-jung.)

656
00:49:16,120 --> 00:49:17,880
I see.

657
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:19,440
Hello.

658
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:22,800
Yes.

659
00:49:23,920 --> 00:49:25,080
Really?

660
00:49:26,960 --> 00:49:28,680
Yes. I'll think about it.

661
00:49:30,320 --> 00:49:31,400
Okay.

662
00:49:32,360 --> 00:49:34,280
I'll give you a call back at this number.

663
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:38,000
Okay. Thank you.

664
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:41,600
What is it? Is it good news?

665
00:49:41,680 --> 00:49:43,360
You're smiling, so it must be good news.

666
00:49:44,240 --> 00:49:47,720
I recently handed in a report
as an assignment.

667
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:49,560
The professor who read it

668
00:49:49,640 --> 00:49:51,680
called to tell me that
I wrote it really well.

669
00:49:52,400 --> 00:49:54,920
I guess professors
these days are really sincere.

670
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,320
Did she call you just to compliment you
about an assignment?

671
00:49:57,400 --> 00:50:00,720
It's not about that.
She's going to publish a book of essays,

672
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:03,240
and she wants to add my writing in it.

673
00:50:03,320 --> 00:50:04,680
She asked me to write something.

674
00:50:05,520 --> 00:50:07,800
I was always a good writer.

675
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:10,200
What does she want you to write about?

676
00:50:10,280 --> 00:50:11,840
An essay on love.

677
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,440
Do you even know what love is?

678
00:50:14,040 --> 00:50:15,520
I don't think you do.

679
00:50:15,800 --> 00:50:17,880
You've never kissed before.

680
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:22,040
To me, that counts as a kiss.

681
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:28,160
Not me.

682
00:51:02,240 --> 00:51:04,160
I'll be waiting on the first floor.

683
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:06,840
Come down when you've settled in.

684
00:51:07,360 --> 00:51:08,440
Come on in.

685
00:51:08,520 --> 00:51:10,680
No, no.

686
00:51:10,880 --> 00:51:12,920
Are you going to shower first?

687
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:17,840
I mean... Are you going to shower

688
00:51:17,920 --> 00:51:19,320
before location scouting?

689
00:51:19,720 --> 00:51:24,000
No.
I'm going to shower before I go to bed...

690
00:51:24,600 --> 00:51:27,960
Right. Yes, people usually shower
before going to bed.

691
00:51:34,520 --> 00:51:36,760
Don't look at me like that
at a place like this.

692
00:51:37,080 --> 00:51:38,160
Not even during the day.

693
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:00,360
Professor Hwang.

694
00:52:04,760 --> 00:52:07,800
You should never come back here again.

695
00:52:08,200 --> 00:52:10,440
-I'm sorry?
-You're fired.

696
00:52:11,520 --> 00:52:15,000
Starting today,
I'll be the one controlling the lab.

697
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:23,320
One moment.

698
00:52:23,560 --> 00:52:26,440
Ms. Na, you should take this call.

699
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:33,840
Hello, this is Na Ha-young.

700
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:35,960
(I know whose voice it is.)

701
00:52:36,040 --> 00:52:38,280
Okay. Go ahead.

702
00:52:59,240 --> 00:53:00,600
Do you think we're going on a picnic?

703
00:53:01,640 --> 00:53:03,880
Did you pack a portable charger?

704
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:07,000
I packed a camera
and something to write notes on too.

705
00:53:07,440 --> 00:53:09,640
I'm a well-prepared assistant director.

706
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:10,960
Sure.

707
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:15,360
Your hat is covering up your face.

708
00:53:15,880 --> 00:53:17,000
Let's go.

709
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:27,480
From there to over there,
people can walk...

710
00:53:27,560 --> 00:53:28,600
Also...

711
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:34,600
-Should I take a picture?
-Yes.

712
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:41,920
The lake and the mountains
look really nice here,

713
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:44,000
so we should take a full shot here.

714
00:53:45,160 --> 00:53:46,720
Hold on. Let me take a picture.

715
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:47,840
Okay.

716
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:07,080
Hello?

717
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:09,320
(-It's me.)
-Yes.

718
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:11,840
I received three tips
about the owner of the voice.

719
00:54:11,920 --> 00:54:13,160
They all named the same person.

720
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:14,760
(It means that it's the right person.)

721
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:16,520
Who is it?

722
00:54:16,600 --> 00:54:17,880
The wife of Chairman Lee Seok-du

723
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:20,400
of Unsung Group, Park Hyo-woo.

724
00:54:22,720 --> 00:54:23,880
(Hello?)

725
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:26,640
Yes. I got it. I'll be right there.

726
00:54:33,160 --> 00:54:36,080
Professor Jo,
I think we found out something

727
00:54:36,160 --> 00:54:38,240
about one of the people inside
the cryonic capsules.

728
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:39,480
-It's--
(-Mr. Ma.)

729
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:41,760
I think Professor Hwang's
memories came back.

730
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:53,120
I have to go back to Seoul.

731
00:54:53,320 --> 00:54:54,520
Did something happen?

732
00:54:54,920 --> 00:54:56,920
A lot has happened.
I'll tell you when I get back.

733
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,080
Stay right in your room.

734
00:54:58,160 --> 00:54:59,840
-Let me come with you.
-No.

735
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:02,440
Stay in your room
and get some rest until I return.

736
00:55:02,520 --> 00:55:04,440
Don't open the door for anyone.

737
00:55:04,760 --> 00:55:07,040
Then I'll keep on
scouting locations by myself.

738
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:09,520
No. What are you talking about?

739
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:11,520
You can't go around alone.

740
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:13,000
Let's go.

741
00:55:17,240 --> 00:55:19,200
You didn't forward the documents
to the police, did you?

742
00:55:19,280 --> 00:55:19,560
(Chief of News Bureau, Na Ha-young)

743
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:20,840
No.
(Chief of News Bureau, Na Ha-young)

744
00:55:21,040 --> 00:55:23,480
Good. I need to double check something.

745
00:55:23,640 --> 00:55:24,800
Also,

746
00:55:25,800 --> 00:55:27,360
there's something I haven't told you.

747
00:55:30,080 --> 00:55:31,360
Professor Hwang

748
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:33,400
is alive.

749
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:43,640
(But Professor Hwang
is acting a little weird.)

750
00:55:44,000 --> 00:55:45,760
(He won't let me near
the cryonics laboratory.)

751
00:57:03,960 --> 00:57:05,000
Professor Hwang.

752
00:57:12,680 --> 00:57:13,880
What are you doing?

753
00:57:14,080 --> 00:57:17,880
I need to destroy all these capsules.

754
00:57:18,120 --> 00:57:20,680
This experiment is a failure.
It's a complete failure.

755
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:23,840
You guys will eventually die as well.

756
00:57:24,680 --> 00:57:26,560
You can't live a normal life.

757
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,920
It's impossible! It just can't happen!

758
00:57:30,120 --> 00:57:31,200
It's

759
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:33,760
all over.

760
00:57:38,960 --> 00:57:40,000
Professor Hwang.

761
00:57:46,440 --> 00:57:47,440
Can you

762
00:57:50,160 --> 00:57:51,280
save us?

763
00:57:57,160 --> 00:57:58,280
Can you

764
00:58:01,680 --> 00:58:02,680
help the two of us

765
00:58:05,200 --> 00:58:08,000
live normal lives?

766
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:10,280
So that we can love each other

767
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:12,200
and

768
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:15,800
roll around in bed and sleep together.

769
00:58:17,440 --> 00:58:19,640
Please help us live

770
00:58:23,200 --> 00:58:24,440
like normal people.

771
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:26,480
Please.

772
00:58:52,640 --> 00:58:53,680
Who is it?

773
00:58:55,680 --> 00:58:56,760
Mr. Ma, is that you?

774
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:17,800
I told you not to open the door
for anyone.

775
00:59:18,560 --> 00:59:21,080
Did something happen?
